00244         switch( parg->arg_mknod3.what.type )

00265         {

00270

00272

00290           {

00299                                                    &attr,
00300                                                    ht, 
00301                                                    pclient, 
00302                                                    pcontext,
00303                                                    &cache_status ) ) != NULL )
00304               {
00305 
00306                   /*
00307                    * Get the FSAL handle for this entry 
00308                    */
00309                   pfsal_handle =  cache_inode_get_fsal_handle( node_pentry, 
00310                                                                &cache_status ) ;
00311                   
00312                   if( cache_status == CACHE_INODE_SUCCESS )
00313                   {
00314                     
00315 #ifdef _DEBUG_MEMLEAKS
00316                     /* For debugging memory leaks */
00317                     BuddySetDebugLabel( "Filehandle V3 in nfs3_mknod" ) ;
00318 #endif  
00319 
00320                     /* Build file handle */
00321                     if( ( pres->res_mknod3.MKNOD3res_u.resok.obj.post_op_fh3_u.handle.data.data_val = Mem_Alloc( NFS3_FHSIZE ) ) == NULL )
00322                       {
00323                         pres->res_mknod3.status = NFS3ERR_IO ;

00330 #endif   
00331 
00332                     if( nfs3_FSALToFhandle( &pres->res_mknod3.MKNOD3res_u.resok.obj.post_op_fh3_u.handle,
00333                                             pfsal_handle, 
00334                                             pexport ) == 0 )
00335                       {
00336                         Mem_Free( (char *)pres->res_mknod3.MKNOD3res_u.resok.obj.post_op_fh3_u.handle.data.data_val ) ;
00337                         pres->res_mknod3.status = NFS3ERR_INVAL;
00338                         return NFS_REQ_OK ;
00339                       }
00340                     else

00343                         pres->res_mknod3.MKNOD3res_u.resok.obj.handle_follows = TRUE ;

00350                         nfs_SetPostOpAttr( pcontext, pexport,

00354

00359                         /*

00371                      
00372                      
00373                     
00374                     return NFS_REQ_OK ;
00375 
00376                   } /* get fsal handle success */
00377                   
00378               } /* mknod sucess */
00379 
00380           } /* not found */
00381         else
00382           {
00383             /* object already exists or failure during lookup */
00384             if( cache_status_lookup == CACHE_INODE_SUCCESS )
